\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $s$
\end_inset

 and for (a) 
\begin_inset Formula $m=1$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $n=2$
\end_inset

 and (b) 
\begin_inset Formula $m=1$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $n=5$
\end_inset

.
 The curves are symmetric under mirror reflexion along the (dotted) straight
 line 
\begin_inset Formula $q_{1}=q_{2}$
\end_inset

, i.e., under the transformation
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $q_{1}\leftrightarrow q_{2}$
\end_inset

.
 The dashed lines in
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

(b) are the hyperbolae
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $q_{1}q_{2}=s^{2m}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset label
